 and the share of involuntary part-time workers in the PSID have similar
 levels and changes, with a correlation coefficient of 0.84.
 The CPS PTER series and our HRS-based measure follow a similar pattern
 during the period of overlap between 1992 and 2012, with a correlation
 coefficient of 0.79.
