 This difference in the average age of the sample may explain why the fraction
 of involuntary part-time workers is lower in the HRS relative to the official
 BLS part-time for econmic reasons measure.
\end_layout

\end_inset

 All three series are highly countercyclical, with more people involuntarily
 working part-time or unable to work up to the ideal number of hours during
 recessions.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Next, we turn to our preferred measure of aggregate labor market hours constrain
ts, which includes full-time workers, plotted in Figure 
